properties.areaDesc: Los Angeles County Coast including Downtown Los Angeles
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued February 16 at 5:41AM PST until February 16 at 9:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility one quarter mile or less in dense fog.

* WHERE...Los Angeles County Coast including Downtown Los
Angeles.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Very low visibility will create dangerous driving
conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Areas affected include much of the L.A.
Basin. Los Angeles Airport reported visibility down to 1/4 mile
as well as Hawthorne Airport. Fog should lift between 7:30-9
AM.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM PST THIS MORNING
